    "Html": "<p>hi,<a id=\"ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_Content_PostRepeater_ctl02_UserNameLink\" href=\"http://www.codeplex.com/site/users/view/dschenkelman\">dschenkelman</a>,</p>\r\n<p>You are right.</p>\r\n<p>But how to implement this scenario:</p>\r\n<div style=\"color:Black;background-color:White\">\r\n<pre><span style=\"color:Blue\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#A31515\">Button</span> <span style=\"color:Red\">Content</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:Black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">Click Me</span><span style=\"color:Black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:Red\">cal:Click.Command</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:Black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">{Binding ClickMe}</span><span style=\"color:Black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">&gt;</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">&lt;/</span><span style=\"color:#A31515\">Button</span><span style=\"color:Blue\">&gt;</span>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When the ClickMe command finish executing, I want to close this View, but I find no way to do it.</p>",
